oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real Photo postacard of four soldiers standing among spent artillery casings
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of four soldiers standing on a pile of spent artillery casings and each is holding one or two casings. All are wearing short overcoats and overseas caps. The soldier on the far right is believed to be Jessie Owen Rice, who served in France. The post card is unused.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Rice, Jessie Owen
